<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:32PM MDT until July 18 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 500 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN PHILLIPS AND NORTHWESTERN VALLEY COUNTIES...
At 431 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles west of
Saco, or 14 miles northeast of Malta, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Saco, Frenchman Reservoir, Bowdoin and Sleeping Buffalo.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
